content: who are the founders of google?
Google was founded by Larry Page and Sergey Brin. They started the company in September 1998 while they were Ph.D. students at Stanford University.
Google's headquarters is located in Mountain View, California, in an area known as Silicon Valley. The headquarters complex is famously referred to as the "Googleplex."
